== 天體的下蜃景 ==
[[File:Inferior_mirage_of_sunset_comet.jpg|[[麥克諾特彗星]]的下蜃景|150px|thumb|left]]
[[File:Omega_Sun_inferior_mirage.jpg|[[夏威夷]]的日沒時呈現Ω型的太陽下蜃景|thumb|150px]]
[[File:Sunset_inferio_mirage.jpg|[[夏威夷]]的日沒時呈現伊特魯里亞花瓶型的太陽下蜃景|thumb|150px]]

[[天體|天體]]的下蜃景是最常見的海市蜃樓，當[[地球|地球]]或[[海洋|海洋]]的表面產生低密度的熱空氣層就會發生下蜃景的現象。在下蜃景會有兩個影像，一個反轉朝下和一個垂直正立朝上的影像。這兩個影像都是從真實物體的幾何方向移動，而正立的影像下沉，倒立的影像則從表面升起。

所有日出和日沒的下蜃景影像都是一樣的保持不變的形狀，一種最著名的形狀是由[[儒勒·凡爾納|儒勒·凡爾納]]命名的伊特魯里亞花瓶<ref name="Jules Verne"> [http://books.google.com/books?ct=result&id=3_ABAAAAQAAJ&dq=Jules+Verne%27s+%E2%80%9CEtruscan+vase%E2%80%9D&ots=WdLjWYdE7s&pg=PA305&lpg=PA305&q=sun#PPA306,M1 Jules Verne: The Green Ray ] Page 305'' tr. by M. de Hauteville</ref>。當大陽正在下沉，伊特魯里亞花瓶的形狀會逐漸的改變；花瓶的瓶頸會變短，直到真實的太陽和蜃景創建出新的形狀——希臘字母的[[Ω|Ω]]。下蜃景的得名就是因為呈現出來的倒立影像在正立影像的下面<ref name="An Introduction to Mirages">[http://mintaka.sdsu.edu/GF/mirages/mirintro.html An Introduction to Mirages] {{Wayback|url=http://mintaka.sdsu.edu/GF/mirages/mirintro.html |date=20100110045709 }} by Andy Young</ref>。

以下是[[儒勒·凡爾納|儒勒·凡爾納]]對[[日沒|日沒]]時的下蜃景所做的描述<ref name="Jules Verne"/>：

:{{Quotation|All eyes were again turned towards the west. The sun seemed to sink with greater rapidity as it approached the sea ; it threw a long trail of dazzling light over the trembling surface of the water ; its disk soon changed from a shade of old gold, to fiery red, and, through their half-closed eyes, seemed to glitter with all the varying shades of a kaleidoscope. Faint, waving lines streaked the quivering trail of light cast on the surface of the water, like a spangled mass of glittering gems. Not the faintest sign of cloud, haze, or mist was visible along the whole of the horizon, which was as clearly defined as a black line traced on white paper. Motionless, and with intense excitement, they watched the fiery globe as it sank nearer and nearer the horizon,and, for an instant, hung suspended over the abyss.Then, through the refraction of the rays, its disk seemed to change till it looked like an Etruscan vase, with bulging sides, standing on the water.
}}

在極罕見的情狀下，可以觀察到除了[[太陽|太陽]]和[[月球|月球]]之外[[天體|天體]]的海市蜃樓影像。一個[[天體|天體]]的[[視星等|視星等]]必須夠低（也就是必須夠亮），才會不僅能看見本體的影像，也能看見海市蜃樓的蜃景。

== 天體的仿蜃景 ==
[[image:Sunset_mirage_111505.jpg|煎餅形狀的下沉太陽]]
[[天體|天體]]的仿蜃景要比下蜃景複雜。一個天體的下蜃景只有兩個海市蜃樓的影像，而仿蜃景可以產生多重的影像，仿蜃景物件的形狀會不斷的改變，而且是不可預測的。為了能出現仿蜃景，冷的空氣會被限制在逆溫層之下，有幾個逆溫層就會產生幾個薄煎餅的形狀<ref name="Sunset Mirage">[http://www.atoptics.co.uk/atoptics/sunmir.htm Sunset Mirages] {{Wayback|url=http://www.atoptics.co.uk/atoptics/sunmir.htm |date=20100125105605 }} Les Cowley</ref>。

[[約書亞記|約書亞記]]可能是最早提到[[太陽|太陽]]的仿蜃景的一本書<ref name="A meteorological anomaly in Palestine 33 centuries ago: How did the sun stop?">{{Cite journal | last = Camuffo | first = D | title = A meteorological anomaly in Palestine 33 centuries ago: How did the sun stop | journal = Theoretical and Applied Climatology | volume = 41 | issue = 1 | pages = 81-85 | publisher = Springer Wien | doi = 10.1007/BF00866205 | date = March 1990 | url = http://www.springerlink.com/content/n03790172366n756/ | accessdate = 2008-04-19 }}{{Dead link|date=2020年2月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。

約書亞整夜行軍前去偷襲[[亞摩利人|亞摩利人]]，引起[[亞摩利人|亞摩利人]]的恐慌並且逃到{{link-en|伯和崙|Bethoron}}，但是他們找不到一個避難所。「被冰雹打死的，比以色列人用刀殺死的還多。」<ref name="The Book of Joshua 10.11">{{Cite web |url=https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Joshua+10&version=CUVMPT |title=約書亞記10:11 |accessdate=2016-05-28 |archive-date=2016-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624195929/https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Joshua+10&version=CUVMPT |dead-url=no }}</ref>"[[冰雹|冰雹]]"是罕見的事件，但在[[沙漠|沙漠]]是要讓日沒的太陽產生仿蜃景或上蜃景的先決條件。下蜃景是在[[沙漠|沙漠]]中最常見的海市蜃樓。當以色列人從炙熱的[[沙漠|沙漠]]到冰雹覆蓋的沙漠與[[亞摩利人|亞摩利人]]戰鬥時，逆溫層可能創造了[[太陽|太陽]]日沒時的仿蜃景。就以色列人來看，太陽似乎提滯不前<ref name="A meteorological anomaly in Palestine 33 centuries ago: How did the sun stop?"/>。在[[約書亞記|約書亞記]]引述了一首詩，太陽還停留在{{link-en|基遍 (古城)|Gibeon (ancient city)|基遍}}，而[[月球|月亮]]在亞雅崙的山谷中，讓約書亞可以完成這一場戰爭<ref name="The Book of Joshua 10.12;10.13">{{Cite web |url=https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Joshua+10&version=CUVMPT |title=約書亞記10:13 |accessdate=2016-05-28 |archive-date=2016-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160624195929/https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Joshua+10&version=CUVMPT |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

