== 新地島效應 ==
{{main|新地島效應}}

由於正常的[[大氣折射|大氣折射]]，太陽光進入地球大氣層時會發生彎曲或折射，不僅使日出發生在太陽升上地平線之前不久；同樣的，日落明顯的也比實際日落稍晚。

在一般的大氣條件下，落日或升起的太陽視位置似乎比其幾何位置高出約半度。但有時，非常不尋常的大氣環境可以使它在地平線下2到5度之間時就可以看見。因為這種效應最早是在[[新地島|新地島]]觀測到，因此被稱為[[新地島效應|新地島效應]]。根據天文學的計算，當時的太陽應該在地平線下兩度

然而，由於氣壓、相對濕度和其他量的變化，而無法預測大氣折射對日出和日落時間的確切影響。還要注意，這種可能的誤差還會隨著緯度的升高（接近兩極）而增加<ref name="Solar Calculator Glossary">{{Cite news| title = Solar Calculator Glossary| publisher = NOAA.gov| url = http://www.srrb.noaa.gov/highlights/sunrise/glossary.html#apparentsunrise| accessdate = 2021-11-12| archive-date = 2012-06-14| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120614071750/http://www.srrb.noaa.gov/highlights/sunrise/glossary.html#apparentsunrise| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

[[Image:Complex_mock_mirage_sunset.jpg|200px]]，但它很好地展示了[[弗里喬夫·南森|弗里喬夫·南森]]在觀察到新地島效應時可能看到的視覺表現。]]

新地島是[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]在[[極區|極區]]的領土。新地島效應是由大氣[[溫躍層|溫躍層]]間的[[陽光|陽光]]高[[折射|折射]]引起的[[海市蜃樓|海市蜃樓]]。新地島效應會給人一種印象，即[[日出|太陽升起]]的比實際應該的時間早，或者[[日落|太陽落下]]的比實際應該的時間晚。
[[弗里喬夫·南森|弗里喬夫·南森]]寫道<ref name="North">{{Cite book| title=Farthest North| url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.167425| last= Nansen| first=Fridtjof| year=1897| pages=[https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.167425/page/n430 394]–395| publisher=Harper & Brothers| location=New York}}</ref><ref name="Annotated bibliography of mirages, green flashes, atmospheric refraction, etc.">{{Cite book| title=Annotated bibliography of mirages, green flashes, atmospheric refraction, etc.| last=Andrew| first=Young| url=http://mintaka.sdsu.edu/GF/bibliog/bibliog.html| access-date=2021-11-12| archive-date=2011-03-09| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110309012628/http://mintaka.sdsu.edu/GF/bibliog/bibliog.html| dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Quotation|The mirage was at first like a flattened-out glowing red streak of fire  on the horizon; later there were two streaks, one above the other, with a  dark space between; and from the main-top I could see four, or even five,  such horizontal lines directly over one another, and all of equal length; as if one could only imagine a square dull-red sun with horizontal dark  streaks across it.  An astronomical observation we took in the afternoon  showed that the sun must in reality have been 2° 22' below the horizon  at noon; we cannot expect to see its disk above the ice before Tuesday at  the earliest; it depends on the refraction, which is very strong in this cold air.
}}

在溫度變化大到足以產生高[[折射|折射]]的任何地方都可以觀察到新地島效應。{{clear}}

